<!-- About Start -->
<div class="container-xxl py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-5">
            
            <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.3s">
                <h1 class="mb-4">
                    EMUS INSTITUTE <br /> Staff Screening, Safeguarding, GDPR & Recruitment Compliance Policies
                </h1>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Owned and Operated by Emus Empower Ltd
                    United Kingdom Registration Number: 17170580
                </p>
                <h6 class="section-title bg-white text-start text-primary pe-3">STAFF CREDENTIAL EVALUATION & COMPLIANCE SCREENING POLICY</h6>
                <p class="mb-4" style="text-align: justify;">
                    <br /> Purpose: To establish procedures for evaluating and verifying prospective staff, workers, facilitators, volunteers, consultants, and affiliated personnel.
                    
                    <br />The policy ensures professional credibility, safeguarding, compliance, and fraud prevention.
                    
                    <br />Applicants may be required to submit educational certificates, identification, CVs, employment references, passport photographs, proof of address, and supporting professional documents.
                    
                    <br />A non-refundable administrative and verification fee of £100 may apply for credential evaluation and compliance screening.
                    
                    <br />The fee may cover credential verification, identity verification, reference checks, safeguarding review, international document review, and administrative processing.
                    
                    <br />Payment of the fee does not guarantee employment or engagement.
                    
                    <br />Submission of false information may result in disqualification or termination.
                </p>
                <br /> 
                <h6 class="section-title bg-white text-start text-primary pe-3">SAFEGUARDING POLICY</h6>
                <p class="mb-4" style="text-align: justify;">
                    <br /> EMUS Institute is committed to safeguarding the welfare and wellbeing of students, staff, volunteers, and vulnerable persons.
                    
                    <br />The Institute promotes safe learning and working environments and maintains safer recruitment procedures.
                    
                    <br />Where legally applicable, DBS checks may be conducted depending on role eligibility.
                    
                    <br />Safeguarding concerns including abuse, harassment, exploitation, discrimination, or neglect should be reported immediately.
                    
                    <br />All personnel are expected to maintain professional conduct and ethical boundaries.
                </p>
                <br />
                <h6 class="section-title bg-white text-start text-primary pe-3">GDPR & DATA PROTECTION POLICY</h6>
                <p class="mb-4" style="text-align: justify;">
                    <br />EMUS Institute is committed to protecting personal data in accordance with UK data protection principles.
                    
                    <br />Personal data collected may include names, contact details, identification documents, academic records, employment records, financial information, and safeguarding information.
                    
                    <br />Data may be processed for recruitment, educational administration, compliance verification, safeguarding, communication, and legal obligations.
                    
                    <br />The Institute shall maintain appropriate security measures and restrict data access to authorized personnel only.
                    
                    <br />Individuals may request access, correction, or deletion of personal data where applicable.
                </p>
                <br />
                <h6 class="section-title bg-white text-start text-primary pe-3">RECRUITMENT & EMPLOYMENT COMPLIANCE POLICY</h6>
                <p class="mb-4" style="text-align: justify;">
                    <br />EMUS Institute promotes equal opportunity and non-discrimination in recruitment and employment.
                    
                    <br />Recruitment procedures may include interviews, document verification, reference checks, credential evaluation, and compliance screening.
                    
                    <br />Applicants may be required to provide evidence of legal authorization to work where applicable.
                    
                    <br />The Institute maintains zero tolerance for fraud, certificate forgery, or falsification of records.
                    
                    <br />Employment offers are subject to successful verification and compliance procedures.
                </p>
                <br />
                <h6 class="section-title bg-white text-start text-primary pe-3"> TERMS OF STAFF SCREENING & VERIFICATION FEES</h6>
                <p class="mb-4" style="text-align: justify;">
                    <br />The Staff Credential Evaluation and Compliance Screening Fee is an administrative charge payable by prospective applicants where applicable.
                    
                    <br />The fee does not constitute payment for guaranteed employment.
                    
                    <br />Except otherwise stated, the fee is generally non-refundable once verification procedures commence.
                    
                    <br />Submission of payment constitutes acceptance of institutional policies and terms.
                </p>

                <br />
                <h6 class="section-title bg-white text-start text-primary pe-3"> POLICY REVIEW </h6>
                <p class="mb-4" style="text-align: justify;">
                    These policies may be reviewed periodically by EMUS Institute management to ensure continued operational 
                    effectiveness and compliance.
                </p>
               

            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<!-- About End -->

